{
    "title": "The 61 Highest-Grossing Movies Of All Time: The Billion-Dollar Club",
    "url": "https://deadline.com/gallery/highest-grossing-movies-all-time/",
    "blocks": [
        {
            "type": "img",
            "content": "https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/billion-gallery.jpg?w=681&h=383&crop=1"
        },
        {
            "type": "p",
            "content": "Universal reached a major milestone in early June when Illumination and Nintendo\u2019s animated sequel The Super Mario Galaxy Movie crossed the $1 billion mark at the global box office. It became the 61st film to hit the three-comma threshold, including its predecessor The Super Mario Bros Movie in 2023."
        },
        {
            "type": "p",
            "content": "RELATED: The Top-Grossing Movies At The Box Office Every Year Since 1977"
        },
        {
            "type": "p",
            "content": "Among the elite list of billion-dollar-grossing films are sequels, Disney remakes and iconic franchises such as Star Wars, Avatar, James Bond, The Lord of the Rings, the Marvel Cinematic Universe, Harry Potter, The Fast & The Furious, Jurassic Park, The Dark Knight, Transformers and Disney and Pixar toons."
        },
        {
            "type": "p",
            "content": "The 2023 summer smash Barbie, starring Margot Robbie and Ryan Gosling, propelled Greta Gerwig into the rankings as the first solo female director to reach the 10-digit milestone. Jennifer Lee hit the billion level with Disney\u2019s Frozen II (2019), co-directing alongside Chris Buck."
        },
        {
            "type": "p",
            "content": "RELATED: The Highest-Grossing Animated Films Of All Time At The Box Office"
        },
        {
            "type": "p",
            "content": "Here\u2019s a look at all of the films that have achieved this remarkable box office milestone."
        },
